paragraph 1: 15. QUARTERLY FINANCIAL INFORMATION (UNAUDITED)
paragraph 2: During the quarter ended December 31, 2019, we purchased a group annuity contract to transfer the pension benefit obligations and annuity administration for a select group of retirees or their beneficiaries to an annuity provider. As a result of the transfer of the pension liability to the annuity provider and other lump sum payments to participants of the Pension Plans, we recognized a non-cash pension settlement charge of $6.7 million during the quarter ended December 31, 2019.
paragraph 3: In 2019, we recognized a gain on extinguishment of debt from the partial repurchase of our Senior Notes of $0.3 million, $1.1 million and $3.1 million during the quarters ended June 30, 2019, September 30, 2019, and December 31, 2019, respectively.
paragraph 4: As part of our integration efforts of FairPoint and continued cost saving initiatives, we incurred severance costs of $8.7 million during the quarter ended December 31, 2019.
